<p>We need to collect Personal Information in order to provide the requested Services to you.  If you do not provide the information requested, we may not be able to provide the Services. If you disclose any Personal Information relating to other people to us or to our service providers in connection with the Services, you represent that you have the authority to do so and to permit us to use the information in accordance with this Privacy Policy.</p>
<p><b>USE OF PERSONAL INFORMATION<br />
</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">We and our service providers use Personal Information for legitimate business purposes, including when you:</span></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Contact us with your questions/comments/ideas/complaints</span></span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">:</span>  We may collect information, depending on the manner in which you contact us (e.g., if you send us an email, we will collect your email address) and the reason for contacting us (e.g., if you have a complaint). In any case, we will collect your contact details so we can respond to your query.<br />
</span>We use this information to manage our contractual relationship with you, when we have a legitimate interest, and/or to comply with a legal obligation.</li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Subscribe to our newsletter/mailing list</span></span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">:</span> We will collect your name and your email address if you wish to subscribe to our newsletter.<br />
</span> We will engage in this activity with your consent or where we have a legitimate interest.</li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">When you translate</span></span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">:</span> When you wish to be a TWB translator, we will ask you to fill in our ‘Translator Application Form’ or our ‘In-Kind Expression of Interest’. Therein we will ask you for the information needed to establish your identity and credentials that show your qualifications to become our translator. This includes your name, your contact details, native language, translating abilities (e.g., which languages you are qualified to translate), and relevant educational and professional experience.<br />
</span> We use this information to manage our business relationship with you.</li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">When you volunteer in another capacity (in-kind)</span></span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">:</span> When you wish to volunteer in another capacity (such as project manager, graphics or web page designer, or you otherwise wish to give your time, technology, and expertise to support us) we will ask you to fill in our ‘Other Volunteer Application Form’. Therein we will ask you for various information, such as your name, your contact details, your area of expertise, and relevant educational and professional experience (CV).<br />
</span>We use this information to manage our business relationship with you.</li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">When you donate as an individual</span></span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">:</span> We will collect your name, contact and address details, donation amount, payment details (such as credit/debit card/PayPal account number), and any other information you voluntarily choose to provide.<br />
</span> We use this information to manage our relationship with you.</li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">When you become a corporate sponsor or partner</span></span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">:</span> We will collect the name of the contact person, contact and address details, sponsorship/invoice amount, payment details (such as bank account, credit/debit card/PayPal account number), and any other information voluntarily provided to us.<br />
</span> We use this information to manage our relationship with you.</li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> When you report a problem with one of our Services</span></span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">:</span> We will collect your first and last names and your contact details so we can respond to your report. You will also need to describe the problem that you have experienced so we can take care of it.<br />
</span> We use this information to manage our contractual relationship with you, when we have a legitimate interest, and/or to comply with a legal obligation.</li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> When you enter into a financial agreement or contract to provide us services:</span></span><span style="font-weight: 400;"> We will collect your first and last names, contact details, bank account details, and identification to confirm that we are not </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">prohibited</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"> from paying you, and residency information to provide to tax authorities.</span></li>
